01:12.600 --> 01:15.649
<i>If you'd have asked me in 1973
if I believed in miracles,</i>

01:15.760 --> 01:18.570
<i>I'd have said absolutely not.</i>

01:18.680 --> 01:20.603
<i>I'd have told you
it's a brutal world out there,</i>

01:20.680 --> 01:22.205
<i>and my only comfort in it</i>

01:22.280 --> 01:24.726
<i>is that I am the master
of my own fate.</i>

01:24.800 --> 01:27.804
<i>I'm the captain of my soul.</i>

01:27.880 --> 01:30.531
<i>Some call what happened
here a miracle,</i>

01:30.600 --> 01:33.285
<i>and there is only
one explanation,</i>

01:33.360 --> 01:37.331
<i>only one way any of this
could've happened.</i>

01:54.120 --> 01:56.043
<i>In the city of Birmingham,</i>

01:56.120 --> 01:58.851
<i>the Department of Justice
some time ago</i>

01:58.920 --> 02:01.287
<i>instituted an investigation,</i>

02:01.360 --> 02:05.410
<i>an attack on the city's
segregation ordinance.</i>

02:05.520 --> 02:09.445
<i>I grew up in Birmingham, Alabama.</i>

02:09.520 --> 02:12.808
Some very, very good friends
of mine were killed by bombs,

02:12.880 --> 02:16.965
<i>bombs that were
planted by racists.</i>

02:17.040 --> 02:19.964
<i>I remember,
from the time I was very small,</i>

02:20.040 --> 02:23.681
<i>I remember the sounds of bombs
exploding across the street,</i>

02:23.760 --> 02:25.410
our house shaking.

02:27.520 --> 02:31.491
<i>So what do you expect
with that type of injustice?</i>

02:31.560 --> 02:33.642
We are angry.

02:33.720 --> 02:35.882
<i>They killed Kennedy. They killed King.</i>

02:35.960 --> 02:37.530
<i>They killed Evers.</i>

02:37.600 --> 02:41.491
<i>I don't think there is
much of a future at this point.</i>

02:41.560 --> 02:43.130
<i>Not much at all.</i>

02:43.200 --> 02:45.487
They're just killing
everybody that wanna...

02:45.600 --> 02:47.568
For the nation itself.

02:47.960 --> 02:50.088
<i>The true picture of
what goes on here</i>

02:50.160 --> 02:51.764
<i>can even be seen
in American television.</i>

02:51.840 --> 02:54.491
<i>If you look at it long enough,
the emptiness,</i>

02:54.560 --> 02:58.690
the spiritual bleakness,
the loss of meaning,

02:58.760 --> 03:00.330
<i>the loss of purpose.</i>

03:00.400 --> 03:02.926
<i>There's no unity in the world.</i>

03:03.000 --> 03:06.561
<i>You couldn't rally 500 people
to sincerely fight</i>

03:06.640 --> 03:08.483
<i>for the same common cause,</i>

03:08.560 --> 03:12.246
<i>no matter what that cause
might be, unless it's dollars.</i>

03:12.320 --> 03:13.924
The result of this is,
of course,

03:14.000 --> 03:15.525
the chaos that we live in.

03:15.600 --> 03:17.284
<i>They set fire to the country.</i>

03:17.360 --> 03:21.081
Get ridiculed, and you know,
discriminated, you know,

03:21.160 --> 03:22.764
and be less than a man.

03:22.840 --> 03:24.649
I don't think
it's right, you know?

03:24.720 --> 03:28.247
<i>I draw the line in
the dust and toss the gauntlet</i>

03:28.320 --> 03:30.288
<i>before the feet of tyranny,</i>

03:30.360 --> 03:35.002
<i>and I say segregation now,
segregation tomorrow,</i>

03:35.080 --> 03:37.526
<i>and segregation forever.</i>

04:14.720 --> 04:16.404
<i>It's a sad day here in Birmingham,</i>

04:16.480 --> 04:17.845
<i>a heartbreaking day,</i>

04:17.920 --> 04:20.048
<i>the Crimson Tide
about to be defeated</i>

04:20.120 --> 04:22.282
<i>by the Trojans
of Southern Cal</i>

04:22.360 --> 04:25.887
<i>and their stellar tailback,
Sam "Bam" Cunningham.</i>

04:25.960 --> 04:30.966
<i>A tough loss for
the Alabama Crimson Tide.</i>

04:36.000 --> 04:37.525
What happened, Coach?

04:37.600 --> 04:39.728
We just got the stew
beat out of us by USC.

04:39.840 --> 04:41.365
You weren't paying attention?

04:41.440 --> 04:43.169
Why'd you bring USC
to Birmingham?

04:43.240 --> 04:44.844
Trying to make some
sort of statement?

04:44.920 --> 04:47.002
That's it, son.

04:56.480 --> 04:59.848
We have a visitor.

04:59.920 --> 05:06.644
<i>Gentlemen, if wanting to win is a fault,</i>

05:06.720 --> 05:09.485
then I plead guilty.
I like to win.

05:09.560 --> 05:11.528
<i>Know no other way.</i>

05:11.600 --> 05:15.047
It's in my blood.

05:15.120 --> 05:21.241
When I get beat, which
is gonna happen occasionally,

05:21.320 --> 05:27.566
I like it to be by an opponent
worthy of my respect.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.604
<i>Fine game, son.</i>

05:34.680 --> 05:36.250
Thank you, sir.

05:36.320 --> 05:38.641
Brave of you to play it.

05:38.720 --> 05:41.530
Thank y'all
for coming down here.

05:46.920 --> 05:48.570
Where you been, Coach?

05:48.640 --> 05:51.723
Talking to a real
football player.

05:51.800 --> 05:53.723
Time and a place
for everything.

05:53.800 --> 05:56.246
Ain't that what
the Good Book says?

06:42.960 --> 06:45.600
<i>In memory of the 10-year
anniversary of the bombing</i>

06:45.640 --> 06:48.769
<i>of the 16th Street
Baptist Church in Birmingham,</i>

06:48.840 --> 06:52.128
<i>here's the late
Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.</i>

06:52.200 --> 06:54.851
<i>What murdered these four girls?</i>

06:54.920 --> 06:58.720
<i>The apathy and the complacency
of many Negro</i>

06:58.800 --> 07:02.407
<i>who will sit down on
their stools and do nothing</i>

07:02.480 --> 07:04.767
<i>and not engage
in creative protests</i>

07:04.840 --> 07:07.286
<i>to get rid
of this evil system.</i>

07:30.880 --> 07:32.291
Tell your mom
I'll be home late.

08:09.920 --> 08:12.491
Nobody forcing you to play.
You know that, right?

08:12.560 --> 08:14.130
You sound like Mama now.

08:14.200 --> 08:15.964
She just don't
wanna see you get hurt.

08:16.040 --> 08:18.008
That's just natural.

08:18.080 --> 08:20.082
Hey, Tony.

08:21.600 --> 08:23.204
Where you live from?

08:26.840 --> 08:28.490
Love you, boy.

08:30.120 --> 08:33.966
<i>I'm frustrated all the
time by what I see,</i>

08:34.039 --> 08:38.250
And wonder when it'll end
and if it ever will end.

08:46.040 --> 08:47.565
What do you think?

08:47.640 --> 08:49.768
It's unbelievable.

08:54.800 --> 08:57.041
What's the name
of the school?

08:57.120 --> 08:58.804
Woodlawn.

09:15.080 --> 09:17.208
<i>Listen up, guys. Listen up.</i>

09:17.280 --> 09:19.647
<i>Morton.</i>

09:19.720 --> 09:21.643
<i>Allyson.</i>

09:21.720 --> 09:24.564
<i>Parker.</i>

09:24.640 --> 09:26.290
<i>Parker?</i>

09:39.920 --> 09:41.922
<i>Anger.</i>

09:43.360 --> 09:45.362
<i>I see it in your faces.</i>

09:47.560 --> 09:51.451
<i>You're angry because of what's
happened to this school.</i>

09:54.720 --> 09:56.722
You've been berated...

09:57.640 --> 09:59.642
...or beaten...

10:00.880 --> 10:02.882
...or shot at.

10:03.760 --> 10:06.001
<i>So have I.</i>

10:06.080 --> 10:08.082
<i>None of us chose this.</i>

10:08.160 --> 10:09.969
<i>It was forced on us.</i>

10:10.040 --> 10:14.045
<i>But we can choose together
what we will do with it.</i>

10:14.120 --> 10:16.805
<i>So, if it is anger
that unites us,</i>

10:16.880 --> 10:19.884
<i>then let's use that anger
to win, boys.</i>

10:22.800 --> 10:28.364
'Cause winning fixes just
about everything, doesn't it?

10:28.480 --> 10:31.529
Are there any questions?

10:33.520 --> 10:35.807
I didn't think so.
Let's go do it.

10:37.520 --> 10:42.367
<i>♪ Sweet home Alabama ♪</i>

10:42.440 --> 10:45.603
<i>♪ Where the skies are so blue ♪</i>

10:45.680 --> 10:47.808
It's not that hot out here, boy.
Come on, let's go!

10:47.880 --> 10:52.169
<i>♪ Sweet home Alabama ♪</i>

10:52.240 --> 10:55.210
<i>♪ Lord, I'm coming home
to you ♪</i>

11:02.880 --> 11:05.884
Stay down, boy.
You don't belong.

11:18.920 --> 11:21.491
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

11:21.560 --> 11:23.608
<i>That's my boy!</i>

11:23.680 --> 11:25.444
- You see that?
- I'm right here, Jerry.

11:25.520 --> 11:27.090
<i>Hey, it's okay, cupcake.</i>

11:27.160 --> 11:28.685
That was just Superman
flying over your head.

11:28.760 --> 11:30.330
<i>It's not your fault.</i>

11:30.400 --> 11:32.050
Watch your mouth, boy!

11:33.160 --> 11:34.685
Hey! Hey!
That's enough!

11:34.760 --> 11:36.922
Suicides, everybody,
thanks to you two.

11:37.000 --> 11:38.000
Let's go.

11:38.040 --> 11:40.771
<i>Look at the man beside you.</i>

11:40.840 --> 11:43.764
<i>This is what happens when
you fight against each other</i>

11:43.840 --> 11:45.968
<i>instead of fighting
to be a team.</i>

11:53.880 --> 11:56.804
You shower when we're done,
Superman.

12:02.560 --> 12:06.963
<i>Over, under, through, and tie.</i>

12:07.080 --> 12:08.889
<i>Let me help you.</i>

12:08.960 --> 12:10.530
I don't wanna go.

12:10.600 --> 12:12.364
<i>It's okay.</i>

12:12.440 --> 12:14.681
Your school is
not like my school.

12:14.760 --> 12:16.410
Will it ever be?

12:18.480 --> 12:20.289
<i>Over, under, through.</i>

12:20.360 --> 12:21.486
Ready?

12:21.560 --> 12:22.721
<i>Yes sir.</i>

12:22.800 --> 12:24.404
Let's go.

12:24.960 --> 12:26.564
<i>See ya, buddy.</i>

12:59.720 --> 13:01.324
Mornin'.

13:01.400 --> 13:03.164
In whose world?

13:05.720 --> 13:12.046
<i>I am Coach Gerelds.</i>

13:12.120 --> 13:16.091
I love football and not science,
so please pay attention

13:16.160 --> 13:19.050
while I give you
all the answers.

13:19.120 --> 13:20.770
<i>Okay, let's get started.</i>

13:20.840 --> 13:22.683
Hey, you gonna quit?

13:22.760 --> 13:24.410
Why?

13:24.480 --> 13:27.723
It's what y'all do.

13:29.520 --> 13:31.170
Come in.

13:31.840 --> 13:34.047
<i>Hey, Coach.</i>

13:34.120 --> 13:37.169
I'm Hank.

13:37.240 --> 13:39.163
So, you're making plays?

13:39.240 --> 13:40.844
Mm-hmm.

13:40.920 --> 13:41.842
Yeah.

13:41.920 --> 13:44.685
Look, I know you're a busy man,
so I'll get right to the point.

13:44.800 --> 13:47.246
<i>I'd like to have a meeting
with your football team.</i>

13:47.320 --> 13:48.970
About what?

13:49.040 --> 13:51.646
Jesus Christ.

13:53.600 --> 13:55.728
Oh, wow, what are you, some
kind of preacher or something?

13:55.800 --> 13:57.848
No, no, not a preacher.

13:57.920 --> 13:59.922
<i>I'm a sports chaplain,
actually.</i>

14:00.000 --> 14:02.844
<i>I like to find different
teams to work with.</i>

14:02.920 --> 14:04.046
<i>I just wanna talk to 'em.</i>

14:04.120 --> 14:07.124
Well, I'm sorry, Hank,
but you can't.

14:10.720 --> 14:12.290
You know this
is a public school?

14:12.360 --> 14:13.566
<i>Yeah.</i>

14:13.640 --> 14:14.641
Yeah, I know.

14:14.720 --> 14:19.009
<i>Look, I've seen some things
all over the country.</i>

14:19.080 --> 14:23.005
I've seen amazing things.

14:23.080 --> 14:26.050
Well, you are
not gonna see them here.

14:26.120 --> 14:28.885
I think your players
could use it.

14:28.960 --> 14:30.086
I think you could too.

14:30.160 --> 14:32.640
Listen, Hank, if my team
needs something,

14:32.720 --> 14:34.722
I will tell you.

14:54.920 --> 14:56.524
Wait up, Johnnie.

14:56.600 --> 14:57.761
<i>So, who is she?</i>

14:57.840 --> 15:00.161
<i>Her name Johnnie, I told you.</i>

15:00.240 --> 15:01.446
<i>That's her real name?</i>

15:01.520 --> 15:03.363
That's the name
she go by.

15:03.440 --> 15:06.444
If you're so curious, why
don't you just ask her yourself?

15:09.000 --> 15:12.163
<i>Of course, that would
require you to actually talk,</i>

15:12.240 --> 15:14.891
or ride the bus
with the rest of us.

15:14.960 --> 15:16.610
I talk.

15:17.520 --> 15:18.965
She don't even
know you exist.

15:19.040 --> 15:20.326
Nobody does.

15:20.440 --> 15:22.488
How she gonna see
what's invisible?

15:22.560 --> 15:23.686
Reggie...

15:41.240 --> 15:43.891
Hey, break it up!

15:46.360 --> 15:48.124
Break it up, now!

16:02.960 --> 16:05.884
I expect you to control
your school, son!

16:05.960 --> 16:07.530
Five hundred kids

16:07.600 --> 16:09.800
getting bussed to a place
every day they don't wanna be.

16:09.840 --> 16:11.444
Twenty-five hundred kids
don't want 'em here.

16:11.520 --> 16:13.284
What did you think
was gonna happen?

16:13.360 --> 16:15.283
What's he talking for?
He ain't got a right here.

16:15.360 --> 16:16.521
- I'm not gonna stand here...
- Let me deal with it.

16:16.600 --> 16:18.329
I don't have to stand here
and be berated

16:18.400 --> 16:19.322
by this gentleman.

16:19.400 --> 16:20.890
- Coach!
- I'm not done!

16:21.000 --> 16:22.968
COACH!
I could arrange that!

16:23.040 --> 16:25.042
<i>Now, who do you
think you are?</i>

16:25.120 --> 16:26.690
Oh yeah, you're
the assistant principal.

16:26.760 --> 16:29.127
Only reason you are that is
'cause we ain't got nobody else.

16:29.200 --> 16:32.204
<i>Now, if you're done, I got
something to say to you.</i>

16:35.320 --> 16:38.802
The national spotlight is off
our city first time in a decade,

16:38.880 --> 16:40.450
<i>so I think it's time
our town</i>

16:40.560 --> 16:42.324
<i>came to its right
and proper balance.</i>

16:42.400 --> 16:47.167
<i>And if that means closing
the doors to this school,</i>

16:47.240 --> 16:49.242
Well, so be it.

16:52.480 --> 16:55.563
We've stayed.

16:55.640 --> 16:58.325
While others have left,
we've stayed.

16:58.400 --> 17:01.404
<i>And we stayed because
we love this school.</i>

17:03.080 --> 17:06.209
<i>This school has been
an enduring beacon</i>

17:06.280 --> 17:10.001
to this city for many years,
and we all know that.

17:10.079 --> 17:11.640
Now, do you really
want its final legacy

17:11.680 --> 17:15.730
to be failed integration?

17:15.800 --> 17:18.644
What would that do?

17:18.720 --> 17:22.122
Why don't you tell me
about that, sir?

17:22.200 --> 17:26.364
All right, Tandy,
I'll tell you.

17:26.480 --> 17:29.563
<i>If there is
one more incident...</i>

17:29.640 --> 17:31.244
...you're done.

17:31.800 --> 17:34.531
<i>Both of you.</i>

17:34.600 --> 17:37.171
Y'all have a nice day.

17:37.240 --> 17:38.890
Thank you, Gene.
You too.

17:38.960 --> 17:40.610
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

17:42.120 --> 17:43.724
Comin'!

17:46.080 --> 17:47.605
Hello?

17:47.680 --> 17:49.250
<i>Hey, babe.</i>

17:49.320 --> 17:51.280
Hey, oh, hey, listen,
Todd's got a Pop Warner game

17:51.320 --> 17:52.970
now on Saturday at 3 p.m.

17:53.040 --> 17:54.565
<i>Now, you tell me
you're gonna be there.</i>

17:54.640 --> 17:56.005
Look, something happened.
I'm okay, but...

17:56.080 --> 17:57.241
<i>What happened?</i>

17:57.320 --> 17:58.481
What always happens.

17:58.560 --> 17:59.482
<i>How bad?</i>

17:59.560 --> 18:02.609
Six went to the hospital.
Knives mostly.

18:03.360 --> 18:04.282
<i>You Okay?</i>

18:04.360 --> 18:06.647
Let's go, Tandy.

18:06.720 --> 18:08.722
Tandy, are you okay?

18:09.880 --> 18:12.645
I gotta go.
Yeah, I'm okay. Bye.

18:12.720 --> 18:14.688
Hey, Coach.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.410
Can I talk to the team now?

18:16.480 --> 18:18.005
Look, I don't have time
to deal with this right now.

18:18.080 --> 18:19.002
Tandy, let's go.
Tandy, now!

18:19.080 --> 18:20.366
Coach!

18:20.440 --> 18:22.602
This is what I do.
I help people.

18:22.680 --> 18:24.569
You know what?
You have five minutes.

18:24.640 --> 18:26.210
After training in the gym.

18:26.280 --> 18:27.964
You talk to Stearns.
You better be good.

18:28.040 --> 18:29.644
Now!

18:29.840 --> 18:31.410
Can I get an introduction?

18:31.480 --> 18:33.130
No.

18:34.280 --> 18:35.640
All right, guys,
let's settle down.

18:35.680 --> 18:36.966
Bring it in.
Guys.

18:37.040 --> 18:38.530
Hey, hey!
Settle down.

18:38.600 --> 18:41.809
<i>We have a motivational speaker
here, if you guys don't mind.</i>

18:41.880 --> 18:43.405
Hey, guys.

18:46.080 --> 18:49.289
I got it.

18:49.360 --> 18:51.010
Good luck.

18:55.920 --> 18:58.571
<i>Hey, everybody.
My name's Hank.</i>

18:58.640 --> 19:00.210
Hey, Hank.

19:00.280 --> 19:03.204
I'm not a coach.
I'm not a teacher.

19:03.280 --> 19:05.362
I'm not a counselor.

19:05.440 --> 19:09.968
<i>In fact, nobody asked me
to come here today.</i>

19:10.040 --> 19:13.408
But I look at what happened
this afternoon, and I think,

19:13.480 --> 19:15.960
"Aren't you sick of it?"

19:16.040 --> 19:17.610
<i>I mean, I'm sick of it.</i>

19:17.680 --> 19:20.286
<i>I'm not even from here,
but does this kind of thing</i>

19:20.360 --> 19:26.606
happen so much
that it just feels normal?

19:26.680 --> 19:30.287
<i>I mean, you don't know me,
you've never seen me before,</i>

19:30.360 --> 19:33.603
but what would you say if I
told you that 100% without fail,

19:33.680 --> 19:36.331
it doesn't have to be this way?

19:39.600 --> 19:45.482
<i>Birmingham has seen
nothing but hate for so long,</i>

19:45.560 --> 19:49.246
<i>it has lost its ability
to believe.</i>

19:49.320 --> 19:52.005
<i>It's lost hope.</i>

19:52.080 --> 19:54.606
<i>Let me tell you
what Jesus said.</i>

19:54.680 --> 20:01.723
<i>He said, "I am the way,
I am the truth, I am the life."</i>

20:02.760 --> 20:05.047
<i>And that means something to me</i>

20:05.120 --> 20:09.603
<i>because I let it mean
something to me.</i>

20:09.680 --> 20:13.765
<i>I'll tell you something else
that seems crazy, only it's not.</i>

20:13.840 --> 20:15.490
<i>I love you.</i>

20:15.560 --> 20:19.121
<i>I care about you,
each and every one of you.</i>

20:19.200 --> 20:22.363
<i>I care about what you've seen.</i>

20:22.440 --> 20:27.970
<i>I care about what
you've been through.</i>

20:28.080 --> 20:32.642
<i>I care about your pain.</i>

20:32.720 --> 20:33.960
So does God.

20:34.040 --> 20:36.520
Jerry, what's going on?
I said 5 minutes.

20:36.600 --> 20:38.170
He's been here
for an hour.

20:38.240 --> 20:39.366
We need to wrap this up.

20:39.440 --> 20:42.011
Tandy, hold on, man.

20:42.080 --> 20:43.366
Man, I know
this sounds crazy,

20:43.440 --> 20:46.762
but just give
the guy a chance.

20:46.840 --> 20:50.003
We ain't got
nothing else to lose.

20:50.080 --> 20:52.765
You don't know me,
but I'm asking you anyway

20:52.840 --> 20:56.606
to stand up right now,
right here,

20:56.680 --> 20:58.967
and make a decision...

20:59.040 --> 21:01.850
<i>...a decision to change,
to forgive,</i>

21:01.920 --> 21:06.926
<i>to be forgiven
no matter what you've done.</i>

21:07.600 --> 21:11.446
That's how much God loves you.

21:11.520 --> 21:17.004
<i>I'm asking you
to choose Jesus.</i>

21:19.520 --> 21:23.320
Can you do that?

21:23.400 --> 21:25.402
Will you do that...

21:28.720 --> 21:33.362
...with me, right now?

21:43.040 --> 21:44.724
Thank you.

22:05.520 --> 22:07.602
Brave men.

22:23.480 --> 22:26.086
What just happened?

22:33.280 --> 22:35.282
Where have you been?

22:36.920 --> 22:38.570
The gym.

22:38.640 --> 22:40.642
And what happened
at the gym?

22:45.160 --> 22:51.770
I let an untrained religious nut
convert the whole team.

22:51.840 --> 22:54.730
<i>I'm going to bed.</i>

22:54.800 --> 22:57.280
The whole team.

23:01.800 --> 23:02.926
Is that good or bad?

23:03.000 --> 23:04.968
<i>I don't know.</i>

23:14.720 --> 23:16.290
<i>Birmingham Post Herald</i>

23:16.360 --> 23:19.364
<i>believes something
about this team.</i>

23:19.440 --> 23:22.091
They believe we're
only gonna win two games.

23:22.160 --> 23:25.528
<i>They believe that this season
is the death rattle</i>

23:25.600 --> 23:29.047
<i>of a school that is
barely able to stay alive.</i>

23:29.120 --> 23:31.964
You see, I don't believe this
for a minute.

23:32.040 --> 23:35.442
I believe that we are
the masters of our own fate.

23:35.520 --> 23:40.367
<i>I believe that we can prove
these people wrong.</i>

23:40.480 --> 23:42.608
<i>Why don't you go out there
and show me</i>

23:42.680 --> 23:44.569
<i>what you all believe?</i>

23:44.640 --> 23:46.244
Let's go do it!

23:53.760 --> 23:55.489
Play our boys!

23:55.560 --> 23:57.210
Come on, Tandy!

23:58.480 --> 24:00.528
<i>Just no win.</i>

24:00.600 --> 24:04.047
Puts them black boys in,
we riot.

24:04.120 --> 24:05.645
<i>He doesn't, they riot.</i>

24:14.680 --> 24:16.011
Bring 'em in, bring 'em in,
bring 'em in!

24:16.080 --> 24:18.082
Bring 'em in!

24:22.320 --> 24:23.970
<i>Play our boys, Tandy!</i>

24:24.040 --> 24:25.883
I know you hear me!

24:25.960 --> 24:28.008
Hey, sit down
and shut up!

24:28.080 --> 24:30.208
<i>Hey, don't talk to my wife like that.</i>

24:30.320 --> 24:32.288
<i>You don't talk to
my wife like that.</i>

24:32.360 --> 24:33.885
I don't expect you to win,

24:33.960 --> 24:36.440
but I expect you
to keep things quiet.

24:36.520 --> 24:38.409
<i>It's not my fault, Owen.</i>

24:38.480 --> 24:39.811
<i>I'm trying to coach football.</i>

24:39.880 --> 24:43.202
<i>This is bigger than football, Tandy.</i>

24:43.280 --> 24:44.930
All right, then.

24:47.120 --> 24:49.088
Get Nathan.

24:49.160 --> 24:50.286
What?

24:50.360 --> 24:52.010
Nathan!

24:52.880 --> 24:55.121
<i>Nathan, let's go.</i>

24:55.200 --> 24:57.601
<i>Come on, son.
Let's go.</i>

24:57.680 --> 25:00.763
<i>That's right.
Our boys wanna play too.</i>

25:02.520 --> 25:04.090
Hey, safety.

25:04.160 --> 25:05.605
Go.

25:21.040 --> 25:22.326
Field wrangler, cover two.

25:22.400 --> 25:23.925
<i>Field wrangler, cover two.</i>

25:24.040 --> 25:25.644
<i>Ready, break!</i>

25:26.520 --> 25:28.443
<i>Nathan!</i>

25:28.520 --> 25:30.090
The slot!

25:30.160 --> 25:32.401
<i>The slot, Nathan!</i>

25:47.920 --> 25:49.570
<i>Hut!</i>

26:01.640 --> 26:03.927
<i>Run! Go, Nathan!
Don't just stand there!</i>

26:04.040 --> 26:05.451
<i>Go, go, go, go, go!</i>

26:27.920 --> 26:29.570
<i>Come on, ref!
That was a late hit!</i>

26:29.640 --> 26:30.766
<i>Are you kidding me?</i>

26:30.840 --> 26:32.490
Come on, Ref!

26:33.800 --> 26:35.450
Welcome to the game.

26:50.440 --> 26:52.920
<i>I thought you said
God was gonna bless us.</i>

26:53.000 --> 26:55.082
<i>I thought we were gonna win.</i>

26:55.160 --> 26:57.606
Maybe God is testing us.

26:57.720 --> 27:01.930
Maybe he wants to know
that our commitment is real,

27:02.000 --> 27:05.607
<i>not just to win
football games.</i>

27:16.880 --> 27:19.326
Look who decided
to ride the bus today.

27:35.160 --> 27:37.640
Hey, Johnnie,
this is Tony.

27:37.760 --> 27:39.762
He don't talk much.

27:39.840 --> 27:41.569
I know who you are.

27:41.680 --> 27:43.205
<i>Really?</i>

27:43.280 --> 27:45.044
<i>So, what you mean
you don't talk, hmm?</i>

27:45.120 --> 27:46.884
It's 'cause you just
ain't got nothing to say

27:46.960 --> 27:48.610
or too afraid to say it?

27:48.680 --> 27:50.205
Both.

27:50.280 --> 27:52.009
<i>Reggie, let him talk.</i>

27:52.080 --> 27:54.606
If you scored,
we would've won the game.

27:54.680 --> 27:56.728
Why you so afraid
of getting hit?

27:56.800 --> 27:58.802
'Cause it hurts.

27:58.880 --> 28:05.764
<i>That's too bad.</i>

28:05.840 --> 28:08.081
Ooh-hoo!

28:16.160 --> 28:18.162
<i>Hey, guys.</i>

28:18.880 --> 28:21.247
Hey, Tony, did you hear
about the meeting tonight?

28:21.320 --> 28:22.970
<i>Fellowship
of Christian Athletes.</i>

28:23.040 --> 28:26.408
<i>Count you in?</i>

28:26.480 --> 28:28.130
What happened
to your foot?

28:28.200 --> 28:30.362
<i>Oh, when I was in college,
I was working part-time</i>

28:30.440 --> 28:32.920
during the summer
at a steel mill.

28:33.000 --> 28:35.207
Accident took away
half my foot

28:35.280 --> 28:38.363
and my dreams of playing
professional baseball.

28:38.440 --> 28:41.762
Man, baseball was everything
to me back then.

28:41.840 --> 28:43.922
Man, I'm sorry about that.

28:44.000 --> 28:46.401
Don't be sorry.

28:46.480 --> 28:50.121
I think that sometimes
before you can have

28:50.200 --> 28:51.725
new dreams in this life,

28:51.800 --> 28:54.963
the old ones have to be
taken away from you.

28:55.040 --> 28:57.964
Look, there's something
I've wanted to say to you

28:58.040 --> 29:01.044
since the first time
I saw you play.

29:02.400 --> 29:05.882
There's something
special about you, Tony.

29:05.960 --> 29:08.088
I can see it.

29:08.160 --> 29:10.003
You have a gift.

29:10.080 --> 29:12.765
That's something
that can't be taught.

29:12.840 --> 29:15.491
That can only be given.

29:15.560 --> 29:22.091
But you have to decide
what you wanna do with it.

29:22.160 --> 29:28.122
When you play for yourself,
you can be great.

29:28.200 --> 29:32.285
But when you play for something
higher than yourself,

29:32.360 --> 29:35.364
that's when something
extraordinary can happen.

29:38.480 --> 29:41.006
God has a purpose
for all of us,

29:41.080 --> 29:42.684
and it is not insignificant.

29:42.800 --> 29:48.921
And obviously, I can't know
what yours is, but I think...

29:50.800 --> 29:54.805
I think God wants you
to be a superstar.

30:01.680 --> 30:03.330
No such thing.

30:03.840 --> 30:05.490
As what?

30:08.400 --> 30:11.165
<i>There's no such thing
as a black superstar.</i>

30:11.240 --> 30:13.641
<i>Not in this state.</i>

30:26.320 --> 30:28.971
You okay, buddy?

30:29.040 --> 30:31.486
I just hate to lose, Dad.

30:31.600 --> 30:33.204
I hate it.

30:33.280 --> 30:36.170
I hate it so bad.

30:36.240 --> 30:39.801
You say you'll do anything
to win, but you won't.

30:39.880 --> 30:41.882
Didn't you see him run?

30:53.800 --> 30:55.450
Hike!

31:00.320 --> 31:01.970
Come on, they're killing us!

31:02.040 --> 31:03.565
If they're not gonna
give him the ball,

31:03.640 --> 31:05.608
this is just a waste
of time, Junior.

31:10.800 --> 31:12.370
<i>We need a new coach!</i>

31:12.440 --> 31:14.329
<i>Tandy, you're in trouble!</i>

31:16.120 --> 31:18.088
<i>Time out. Time out.</i>

31:18.160 --> 31:20.447
<i>Boys, bring it in.
Come here.</i>

31:21.960 --> 31:25.248
<i>Nathan, come here.</i>

31:25.360 --> 31:27.488
This your time
to shine, let's go.

31:29.320 --> 31:30.845
That a boy, Tony!

31:30.920 --> 31:32.649
Okay, Nathan's
in at tailback.

31:32.720 --> 31:33.881
<i>Wait, wait, Coach!</i>

31:33.960 --> 31:35.166
Power I, guys.

31:35.240 --> 31:36.446
Eleven yards,
that's what I need, okay?

31:36.520 --> 31:38.284
That's my position!
He don't know the offense yet!

31:38.360 --> 31:40.249
Morton!
This is my team!

31:40.320 --> 31:44.291
<i>It's not a democracy!
Now go sit down!</i>

31:48.200 --> 31:49.770
<i>All right, let's go.</i>

31:49.840 --> 31:51.842
<i>Nathan.</i>

31:54.240 --> 31:56.129
You know what I believe?

31:56.200 --> 32:00.842
That you are faster than them,
so you show me.

32:00.920 --> 32:02.684
Yes, sir.

32:04.880 --> 32:06.530
Tandy!

32:29.480 --> 32:31.369
This is a contact sport,
okay?

32:31.440 --> 32:33.204
When someone wants to hit you,

32:33.280 --> 32:35.726
it feels good to hit 'em
first, okay? Try it.

32:35.800 --> 32:37.325
<i>Atta boy, Tony!</i>

32:37.400 --> 32:39.004
Gonna be 1st down
right now!

32:39.080 --> 32:40.684
Tandy, put my boy in.

32:40.760 --> 32:42.649
You're killing us!

32:47.560 --> 32:49.164
Break!

33:07.920 --> 33:09.922
That's my baby!

33:16.400 --> 33:18.641
All right,
let's punch it in.

33:18.720 --> 33:20.722
<i>Nathan, out.</i>

33:22.360 --> 33:24.010
<i>Nice one, 22!</i>

33:24.760 --> 33:26.330
Hey, Tony.

33:26.440 --> 33:27.680
How'd that feel?

33:27.760 --> 33:29.410
Good.

33:31.240 --> 33:33.129
Really good.

33:39.800 --> 33:41.370
Come here, baby!

33:41.440 --> 33:43.169
Momma is so proud of you.

33:43.240 --> 33:45.083
Great game, son.
Great game.

33:45.160 --> 33:46.730
Who is this?

33:46.800 --> 33:48.450
This is Johnnie.

33:48.520 --> 33:50.170
Hi.

33:50.240 --> 33:52.208
Oh, she sure is
pretty, Tony.

33:52.280 --> 33:53.406
Oh, it's not like that.

33:53.480 --> 33:54.970
What church you go to?

33:55.040 --> 33:56.166
Momma!

33:56.240 --> 33:58.049
No girl better even think
about marrying my Tony

33:58.120 --> 33:59.724
without being church-going.

33:59.800 --> 34:01.325
I don't go to church.

34:01.400 --> 34:03.323
<i>Well, you gonna
go to church with us.</i>

34:03.400 --> 34:04.970
<i>And I see I'm a have
to fatten you up,</i>

34:05.040 --> 34:06.371
'cause I don't know
how you think you gonna

34:06.480 --> 34:09.324
have my grandbabies
with hips like that.

34:10.400 --> 34:11.925
<i>Uh, let's just let them be.</i>

34:12.000 --> 34:14.128
Yeah, well a closed mouth
don't get fed, Junior.

34:15.080 --> 34:17.047
I want my boy
to play college ball.

34:17.120 --> 34:18.724
All right,
he has that opportunity,

34:18.800 --> 34:20.960
and I don't think it's right
that it's being taken away

34:21.000 --> 34:22.603
by somebody
who don't even belong.

34:22.679 --> 34:24.444
I coach the team
that I am given, Bull.

34:24.520 --> 34:26.090
I coach to win.

34:26.159 --> 34:27.685
That is my commitment
to myself, this school,

34:27.760 --> 34:30.127
and every parent in it,
including you.

34:30.760 --> 34:33.081
Hey.
Hey!

34:33.159 --> 34:36.083
You gonna get
that colored boy hurt.

34:40.480 --> 34:42.608
Therefore,
since we are surrounded

34:42.679 --> 34:45.524
by such a great cloud
of witnesses,

34:45.600 --> 34:49.206
let us lay aside
every weight.

34:49.280 --> 34:53.888
<i>We have to run this race
called life with patience.</i>

34:53.960 --> 34:57.601
<i>Are you willing to run the race
and put down the shame?</i>

34:57.680 --> 34:59.330
<i>Amen!</i>

34:59.400 --> 35:01.323
<i>Turn to your neighbor
and say, "Put it down."</i>

35:01.400 --> 35:02.526
Put it down!

35:02.600 --> 35:05.729
How many of y'all have a race
you know you got to run?

35:07.880 --> 35:12.568
<i>You think 'cause you
got that many races to run.</i>

35:12.640 --> 35:15.041
<i>We need those
that will accomplish</i>

35:15.120 --> 35:18.124
<i>all God has laid before us.</i>

35:18.200 --> 35:21.443
<i>We need a man,
a woman, or someone...</i>

35:21.520 --> 35:23.249
Finally.

35:23.320 --> 35:24.890
Amen, Pastor!

35:24.960 --> 35:26.564
<i>Because they're looking at you.</i>

35:26.640 --> 35:28.165
<i>Because they're
looking to the church.</i>

35:28.240 --> 35:29.810
<i>Because they're
looking to a better day.</i>

35:29.880 --> 35:31.530
<i>Because they're
looking to a new day.</i>

35:31.600 --> 35:34.444
Why? Because
it's time to rise up!

35:34.520 --> 35:36.045
Rise up!

35:36.120 --> 35:39.841
Somebody's gotta
rise up this morning!

35:46.800 --> 35:48.450
Rise up.

35:48.520 --> 35:50.090
You buy all that stuff?

35:50.160 --> 35:53.209
<i>Yeah, I do.</i>

35:53.280 --> 35:55.931
Been taught it all my life.

35:56.000 --> 36:00.642
I finally feel like I own it,
like it's mine.

36:00.760 --> 36:02.410
What about you?

36:02.480 --> 36:06.201
I'm Christian same
as the next person,

36:06.280 --> 36:08.965
but I believe rising up
means fighting back,

36:09.040 --> 36:11.202
only way things
are gonna change.

36:11.280 --> 36:15.649
Tony, we in a system that
prevents any type of aspiration,

36:15.720 --> 36:17.324
any type of growth.

36:17.400 --> 36:18.526
Johnnie...

36:18.600 --> 36:19.931
And then when one of us
can't take it anymore,

36:20.000 --> 36:21.445
we're made an example of.

36:21.520 --> 36:22.760
We take the blame.

36:22.840 --> 36:23.762
Hey, Johnnie!

36:23.840 --> 36:25.330
Nuh-uh, but the blame
belongs in the system,

36:25.400 --> 36:27.129
the system that's been keeping
us down time after time.

36:27.200 --> 36:29.202
Johnnie Francis!

36:31.320 --> 36:33.209
Go out with me.

36:33.280 --> 36:35.442
What?

36:35.520 --> 36:37.090
Friday night.

36:37.160 --> 36:38.730
Okay, fine.

36:38.840 --> 36:40.365
I'll pick you up?

36:40.440 --> 36:42.010
Nuh-uh
I'll meet you there.

36:42.080 --> 36:43.684
I'll pick you up.

36:43.760 --> 36:45.842
I'll meet you there.

36:45.920 --> 36:48.764
Rising up still means
fighting back.

36:53.160 --> 36:55.128
All right, let's bow our heads.

36:55.200 --> 36:57.089
Dear God,
thank you for this day.

36:57.160 --> 36:58.889
<i>Thank you for this chance
to play football</i>

36:58.960 --> 37:00.564
<i>and fellowship together.</i>

37:00.640 --> 37:02.563
<i>And we hope that we
honor you and your glory.</i>

37:02.640 --> 37:05.530
In Jesus' name, amen.

37:05.600 --> 37:07.523
Let's go, man.
Come on.

37:08.600 --> 37:10.443
<i>First team O, first team D,
let's go.</i>

37:15.800 --> 37:17.529
Well, he's paying attention.

37:17.600 --> 37:22.686
He's paying attention now,
and that's the whole thing.

37:22.800 --> 37:24.450
Excuse me.

37:28.760 --> 37:31.411
Amen.

37:32.920 --> 37:34.524
So, you're all in, huh?

37:34.600 --> 37:36.125
Yep.

37:36.200 --> 37:37.770
You are?

37:37.840 --> 37:39.410
Yeah.

37:39.480 --> 37:42.609
All right, then.

37:42.680 --> 37:44.250
You know, we're meeting
with the players tonight

37:44.320 --> 37:46.641
over at Crestwood.

37:46.720 --> 37:48.290
You should come.

37:48.360 --> 37:50.362
If it was my neighborhood,
maybe.

37:50.440 --> 37:52.363
But Crestwood, come on,
you know it's only gonna be

37:52.440 --> 37:54.010
white players there, Jerry.

37:54.080 --> 37:56.731
I mean, what's that
gonna achieve?

37:58.520 --> 38:00.443
Shorty White, 2 o'clock.

38:02.920 --> 38:03.842
Whoo!

38:03.920 --> 38:05.922
I give you 30 seconds.

38:06.000 --> 38:08.128
I'll give him
less than that.

38:08.200 --> 38:10.009
<i>We're coming after you, Tandy.</i>

38:10.080 --> 38:13.243
<i>Ooh, 8 more weeks
'til judgment day.</i>

38:13.320 --> 38:15.721
Glorious rivalry day.

38:15.800 --> 38:18.883
Banks' Jets coming at you
from the clouds.

38:18.960 --> 38:20.564
<i>I'm bringing my
white knight, son.</i>

38:20.640 --> 38:24.440
<i>I know you know who he is,
Mr. Jeff Rutledge.</i>

38:24.520 --> 38:27.000
He's only the best
quarterback in the state, folks.

38:27.080 --> 38:29.082
Birmingham News printed that.

38:29.200 --> 38:30.725
<i>I didn't say it.</i>

38:34.080 --> 38:40.087
<i>♪ Simple kind of man ♪</i>

38:40.160 --> 38:46.725
<i>♪ Oh, be something you
love and understand ♪</i>

38:47.720 --> 38:54.729
<i>♪ Baby, be a simple
kind of man ♪</i>

38:56.200 --> 38:58.362
<i>♪ Won't you do this
for me, son... ♪</i>

38:58.480 --> 39:00.482
Hey, Coach.

39:01.680 --> 39:03.728
Good to see you.

39:03.800 --> 39:05.723
Ain't never seen
a house this big.

39:05.800 --> 39:07.802
No, me neither.

39:09.520 --> 39:11.010
You coming in?

39:11.080 --> 39:12.286
You go ahead.

39:12.360 --> 39:14.362
I'm just gonna have
a quick smoke.

39:15.840 --> 39:17.683
You really should.

39:17.760 --> 39:20.127
It's pretty cool.

39:50.560 --> 39:53.928
<i>Well, Shorty White
beat 'em two seasons ago.</i>

39:54.000 --> 39:57.447
<i>Golly, how many'd
they dress, a hundred?</i>

39:57.520 --> 39:59.522
<i>They got three times our budget
and a new stadium.</i>

39:59.600 --> 40:01.602
<i>I don't see how that's fair.</i>

40:02.600 --> 40:07.447
We need to redefine winning.

40:07.520 --> 40:09.090
Like a field goal, right?

40:09.160 --> 40:12.448
I mean, no one's scored on 'em
this whole season,

40:12.520 --> 40:14.807
and a field goal, bam,
that's winning.

40:14.880 --> 40:18.885
<i>Jerry, is this real?</i>

40:20.080 --> 40:22.367
How does a whole team
convert?

40:22.480 --> 40:24.642
<i>How is it that the only
place in the whole city</i>

40:24.720 --> 40:26.722
<i>that blacks and whites get
along is my football team?</i>

40:26.800 --> 40:28.370
Why are you so cynical?

40:28.440 --> 40:32.968
Because I believe
in what I can see.

40:33.040 --> 40:38.444
With all due respect, Coach,
you might start looking around.

40:39.320 --> 40:41.402
Hey, we're gonna
win this thing.

40:41.480 --> 40:43.050
- Oh, here we go.
- Really?

40:43.120 --> 40:44.645
<i>We're gonna win this game,</i>

40:44.720 --> 40:46.643
and I've got something
I wanna say to the team.

40:46.720 --> 40:48.370
Whoo!
Woodlawn!

40:48.440 --> 40:50.090
Whoo!

40:51.080 --> 40:52.605
<i>Welcome back, everybody.</i>

40:52.720 --> 40:54.688
<i>This is WXJC Birmingham,
and we're following</i>

40:54.760 --> 40:56.649
<i>the number-one team
in the state,</i>

40:56.720 --> 41:00.088
<i>the Huffman Vikings,
on their so-far uncontested road</i>

41:00.160 --> 41:01.844
<i>to another championship.</i>

41:01.920 --> 41:04.764
Now, tonight, they square off
against the Woodlawn Colonels,

41:04.840 --> 41:08.606
and this should be a routine,
regular season ball game,

41:08.680 --> 41:10.489
as they're favored
by 6 touchdowns.

41:10.560 --> 41:13.564
