<i>Okay, come on, men.
Everyone take a knee.</i>

01:02:42.400 --> 01:02:45.609
Our Father who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

01:02:46.560 --> 01:02:48.449
Jesus can't save you now,
fellas.

01:02:48.520 --> 01:02:50.568
This is Jets football!

01:02:52.640 --> 01:02:54.210
Jesus can't save you now!

01:02:54.280 --> 01:02:55.884
You're going down!

01:02:57.120 --> 01:02:58.724
Amen.

01:03:00.400 --> 01:03:01.322
Boys, you ready to beat Banks?

01:03:01.400 --> 01:03:02.322
Yes, sir!

01:03:02.400 --> 01:03:03.526
I said are you ready
to beat Banks?

01:03:03.600 --> 01:03:04.522
Yes, sir!

01:03:04.600 --> 01:03:06.250
One, two, three, believe!

01:03:23.880 --> 01:03:25.928
<i>A devastating hit on Tony Nathan,</i>

01:03:26.000 --> 01:03:30.164
<i>and he is getting up slowly
at the 30-yard line.</i>

01:03:30.240 --> 01:03:31.810
Their gunnin' for him.

01:03:40.760 --> 01:03:42.410
<i>Hike!</i>

01:03:50.760 --> 01:03:53.127
I know, Jerry.
I know.

01:03:55.000 --> 01:03:56.650
Come on, boy.

01:04:01.440 --> 01:04:05.843
<i>Nathan looks right,
then left, nowhere to go.</i>

01:04:13.480 --> 01:04:15.608
High left, 4-24 draw.

01:04:18.280 --> 01:04:19.884
Hike!

01:04:34.040 --> 01:04:35.690
<i>He is short.</i>

01:04:57.200 --> 01:04:59.362
Down set.

01:04:59.440 --> 01:05:01.090
Blue 18.

01:05:01.440 --> 01:05:03.010
Blue 18.

01:05:03.080 --> 01:05:04.684
Hike!

01:05:11.600 --> 01:05:13.250
Excuse me, Coach.

01:05:14.600 --> 01:05:16.762
Can't guard perfect, Coach.

01:05:16.840 --> 01:05:18.729
<i>Get 41.
Forty-one!</i>

01:05:18.800 --> 01:05:20.802
Down set!

01:05:20.880 --> 01:05:22.769
<i>Hike!</i>

01:05:25.600 --> 01:05:27.841
<i>Middle, middle, middle!</i>

01:05:29.680 --> 01:05:31.205
<i>Touchdown!</i>

01:05:47.240 --> 01:05:49.527
<i>Get out there, boys.</i>

01:05:53.800 --> 01:05:55.689
You silence them, Nathan.

01:05:55.760 --> 01:05:57.808
Nathan, you silence them.

01:05:57.880 --> 01:05:59.644
You get out there,
and you shut them up.

01:05:59.720 --> 01:06:01.961
Come on, get it done.
Come on!

01:06:04.200 --> 01:06:06.885
That's just football, boys.
Little bit of rain.

01:06:06.960 --> 01:06:08.689
Power C Waggle left on one.
On one.

01:06:08.760 --> 01:06:10.808
Ready, break.

01:06:16.720 --> 01:06:18.290
Hike!

01:06:32.360 --> 01:06:34.249
Get up, son.

01:06:55.600 --> 01:06:58.809
<i>Hey, Danny!
You stop him right here.</i>

01:06:58.880 --> 01:07:00.530
You hear me?

01:07:09.400 --> 01:07:12.051
You make 'em pay, son.
Right here!

01:07:24.560 --> 01:07:26.085
<i>He's still on his feet.</i>

01:07:26.160 --> 01:07:27.730
<i>He's in the 20, the 15,</i>

01:07:27.800 --> 01:07:29.165
<i>working his way
through the defense</i>

01:07:29.240 --> 01:07:30.605
<i>toward the end zone.</i>

01:07:30.680 --> 01:07:33.206
<i>He's willing his way forward.
He scores.</i>

01:07:33.280 --> 01:07:36.966
<i>Touchdown, Woodlawn.</i>

01:07:52.680 --> 01:07:54.648
Break it up!
Break it up!

01:08:09.200 --> 01:08:11.202
Atta boy, atta boy,
atta boy, atta boy.

01:08:11.280 --> 01:08:13.009
Hey, that flag
don't hurt me.

01:08:13.080 --> 01:08:15.082
That flag don't hurt me.

01:08:25.960 --> 01:08:27.529
<i>Doc!</i>

01:08:27.600 --> 01:08:30.604
Coach, think we'll be taking
a big risk to let him play.

01:08:33.680 --> 01:08:37.241
Nathan, we win with you.

01:08:37.319 --> 01:08:40.005
We cannot win without you.
You understand?

01:08:40.080 --> 01:08:41.604
Tony!

01:08:41.720 --> 01:08:43.721
Adversity is a crucible
of greatness.

01:08:47.640 --> 01:08:48.880
Yes, sir.

01:08:48.960 --> 01:08:50.086
Can you do this?

01:08:50.160 --> 01:08:51.082
Yes, sir.

01:08:51.160 --> 01:08:54.607
Okay, let's do it.
Come on.

01:09:03.080 --> 01:09:04.729
Nathan!

01:09:06.279 --> 01:09:08.408
Let's go.

01:09:11.720 --> 01:09:14.041
<i>Hey Coach, has it rained harder?</i>

01:09:14.120 --> 01:09:15.804
Them angels is crying!

01:09:16.240 --> 01:09:18.129
Them angels is crying!

01:09:55.960 --> 01:10:00.602
I just wanna say that
I am proud of all of you.

01:10:04.120 --> 01:10:07.124
<i>I'm proud of each
and every one of you,</i>

01:10:10.320 --> 01:10:16.168
for the game that
you played tonight

01:10:16.240 --> 01:10:20.529
and the men that you
have become this season.

01:10:35.480 --> 01:10:39.041
Hank, come on, just...
you say something.

01:11:18.760 --> 01:11:21.923
Hey, hey, come here.
Come here, come here, come here.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:24.321
Why didn't you play me?

01:11:24.400 --> 01:11:28.405
You know what is more important
than winning football games?

01:11:28.480 --> 01:11:30.130
You are.

01:11:31.560 --> 01:11:33.369
You are.

01:11:34.160 --> 01:11:36.447
You are.

01:11:46.360 --> 01:11:50.729
<i>Jesus says to love our enemies.</i>

01:11:50.800 --> 01:11:55.010
<i>We have to love
those that oppose us.</i>

01:11:55.120 --> 01:11:59.523
<i>We have to love those
that are against us,</i>

01:11:59.600 --> 01:12:04.049
<i>to do good to those
that persecute us.</i>

01:12:04.120 --> 01:12:10.480
<i>This is the kind of love that
isn't easy, but if we do it,</i>

01:12:10.560 --> 01:12:13.040
we will see change like
we have never seen before.

01:12:13.120 --> 01:12:14.929
Because here's the question.

01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:19.403
If you only love those
that love you back,

01:12:19.520 --> 01:12:24.003
what kind of love is that?

01:12:24.080 --> 01:12:25.844
<i>Amen!</i>

01:12:25.920 --> 01:12:28.321
<i>Think about it, church.</i>

01:12:28.400 --> 01:12:30.129
Think about it.

01:12:31.080 --> 01:12:32.650
<i>I can do pork chops.</i>

01:12:32.720 --> 01:12:34.290
I'm gonna fry 'em up
in some flour.

01:12:34.360 --> 01:12:36.567
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:12:50.160 --> 01:12:52.162
What in the world?

01:12:52.560 --> 01:12:55.086
That's Bear Bryant.

01:12:58.240 --> 01:13:00.004
<i>Hello, son.</i>

01:13:00.080 --> 01:13:01.650
<i>I'm Coach Bryant.</i>

01:13:01.720 --> 01:13:03.324
I know.

01:13:04.520 --> 01:13:06.602
<i>Junior, get the baby.</i>

01:13:15.400 --> 01:13:18.290
<i>Did you always wanna be a coach?</i>

01:13:18.360 --> 01:13:20.328
My mama wanted me
to be a preacher,

01:13:20.400 --> 01:13:23.006
but I told her that
coaching and preaching

01:13:23.080 --> 01:13:24.605
is pretty much
the same thing.

01:13:24.680 --> 01:13:28.810
We both serve something
greater than ourselves.

01:13:28.880 --> 01:13:32.248
She went for it.

01:13:32.320 --> 01:13:34.322
<i>Oh, I could eat
that whole thing.</i>

01:13:36.440 --> 01:13:40.126
<i>You know, a great team
shares the same heartbeat.</i>

01:13:40.200 --> 01:13:41.770
That's what I believe.

01:13:41.840 --> 01:13:44.161
Amen.

01:13:44.240 --> 01:13:48.882
<i>If there is one thing
that has helped me as a coach,</i>

01:13:48.960 --> 01:13:52.885
<i>Louise, it's my ability
to recognize winners,</i>

01:13:52.960 --> 01:13:54.530
or good people
who can become winners.

01:13:54.600 --> 01:13:57.888
And that's what I see
when I look at you, Tony.

01:13:57.960 --> 01:13:59.724
And I'm talking about
winning in the larger sense.

01:13:59.800 --> 01:14:02.929
I'm talking about character.

01:14:03.040 --> 01:14:05.805
Now, you have
a strong family.

01:14:05.920 --> 01:14:08.321
That's a great advantage.

01:14:08.400 --> 01:14:11.563
And you're coached
by a special coach.

01:14:11.640 --> 01:14:13.881
Thank you, sir.

01:14:13.960 --> 01:14:15.610
So, you coming?

01:14:15.720 --> 01:14:19.122
Where?

01:14:19.200 --> 01:14:21.407
'Bama.

01:14:21.480 --> 01:14:24.165
<i>My coach, he played at Auburn.</i>

01:14:24.240 --> 01:14:25.401
<i>Son...</i>

01:14:29.160 --> 01:14:30.969
<i>...don't you want
one of these?</i>

01:14:31.040 --> 01:14:32.610
Sure do.

01:14:32.680 --> 01:14:35.331
Louise, he ain't gonna
get one at Auburn.

01:14:35.400 --> 01:14:38.802
<i>I feel sorry for those boys.</i>

01:14:38.880 --> 01:14:44.330
How many
black players you got?

01:14:44.400 --> 01:14:49.008
Well, we got Wilber Jackson,
and he's a stud.

01:14:49.080 --> 01:14:52.527
<i>But I don't have white players
and black players.</i>

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:54.329
I have football players.

01:14:54.400 --> 01:14:57.847
That's how I see it.

01:14:57.920 --> 01:15:03.484
But in answer to your question,
not nearly enough.

01:15:03.600 --> 01:15:06.604
<i>So, why do you
see that changing?</i>

01:15:07.880 --> 01:15:09.882
Because it's time.

01:15:13.240 --> 01:15:15.288
Are you gonna help me?

01:15:33.920 --> 01:15:39.404
Football just hurts me
and everybody around me.

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:45.804
Nobody's forcing you
to play football.

01:15:45.880 --> 01:15:48.406
You know that, right?

01:15:48.520 --> 01:15:54.527
You can walk away right now
and let the world pass on by.

01:15:54.600 --> 01:15:57.490
But this is bigger
than football, ain't it?

01:15:57.560 --> 01:15:59.210
Yes, sir.

01:16:01.440 --> 01:16:05.968
Some kinda great power
been given to you, son.

01:16:06.080 --> 01:16:08.367
I can see it in
them kids' faces.

01:16:08.440 --> 01:16:11.011
I know what they're thinking.

01:16:11.080 --> 01:16:14.368
"A black star like you
at a white high school?

01:16:14.440 --> 01:16:19.002
If he can do it, so can I."

01:16:19.080 --> 01:16:21.811
That is your gift.

01:16:21.880 --> 01:16:26.363
This is your time
to do as you choose.

01:16:26.440 --> 01:16:30.331
And that's a lot to carry.

01:16:30.400 --> 01:16:33.449
So tell me what to do,
and I'll do it.

01:16:39.400 --> 01:16:41.323
<i>The Good Book says</i>

01:16:41.400 --> 01:16:45.291
<i>"When there is no vision,
the people perish."</i>

01:16:45.360 --> 01:16:48.728
<i>That means people
can't live without hope.</i>

01:16:48.800 --> 01:16:52.725
<i>They need it
like they need air.</i>

01:16:52.800 --> 01:16:54.450
<i>I say...</i>

01:16:55.000 --> 01:16:57.002
<i>...go give it to 'em.</i>

01:17:02.720 --> 01:17:04.290
Tony.

01:17:04.360 --> 01:17:06.089
You all know Tony Nathan.

01:17:06.160 --> 01:17:08.208
He set this up.

01:17:08.280 --> 01:17:09.850
Thanks Jeff.

01:17:09.920 --> 01:17:12.127
This is Hank.
He's got something to say.

01:17:12.200 --> 01:17:15.921
<i>Thank you very much, Mr. Rutledge.</i>

01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:19.971
We found something
at Woodlawn.

01:17:20.040 --> 01:17:21.644
Something that's bigger
than winning.

01:17:21.720 --> 01:17:24.610
<i>It's bigger than football.</i>

01:17:24.680 --> 01:17:26.364
<i>It's why we're here.</i>

01:17:26.440 --> 01:17:30.206
<i>It's bigger than this rivalry.</i>

01:17:30.280 --> 01:17:31.805
We wanna share it with you.

01:17:31.880 --> 01:17:37.205
We wanna schedule a meeting with
your entire team and your coach.

01:17:43.440 --> 01:17:45.010
You think this
school'll understand

01:17:45.080 --> 01:17:46.650
what we're doing here?

01:17:46.720 --> 01:17:49.724
They won't understand,
and that's okay.

01:17:51.800 --> 01:17:53.802
Boys.

01:17:57.560 --> 01:17:59.210
<i>Coach!</i>

01:17:59.840 --> 01:18:02.320
Shorty, Hank,
what's this all about?

01:18:05.880 --> 01:18:07.928
We finally had
our first meeting,

01:18:08.000 --> 01:18:09.729
that tent revival thing.

01:18:09.800 --> 01:18:11.802
<i>Jeff set it up
over at the church.</i>

01:18:11.880 --> 01:18:14.121
I went to shut it down
anyway,

01:18:14.200 --> 01:18:16.601
<i>'cause I thought Jesus
would make my boys weak.</i>

01:18:16.680 --> 01:18:18.250
<i>Next thing you know,</i>

01:18:18.320 --> 01:18:19.920
I'm the first one
walking down the aisle,

01:18:19.960 --> 01:18:24.363
crying like a child,
my whole team behind me.

01:18:24.440 --> 01:18:26.169
<i>My whole team.</i>

01:18:26.240 --> 01:18:27.810
<i>How does that happen?</i>

01:18:27.880 --> 01:18:29.405
<i>You gotta see it
with your own eyes.</i>

01:18:29.480 --> 01:18:31.767
Unbelievable.

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:33.842
I'm a changed man...

01:18:35.280 --> 01:18:37.408
...and I'm sorry.

01:18:37.480 --> 01:18:38.686
Fine.

01:18:38.760 --> 01:18:39.886
I will take it.

01:18:39.960 --> 01:18:41.803
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:18:41.880 --> 01:18:43.450
I'm glad that's over.

01:18:43.520 --> 01:18:47.127
We are gonna do camp
a little different this year.

01:18:47.240 --> 01:18:50.528
Yeah, just a little bit
different.

01:18:50.600 --> 01:18:55.891
<i>You wanna do something wild,
something truly rebellious?</i>

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:59.721
I like that.

01:18:59.800 --> 01:19:02.280
I want you to do something
that's never been done before.

01:19:02.360 --> 01:19:04.044
At least, not to my knowledge.

01:19:21.440 --> 01:19:24.569
<i>♪ Prepare yourself,
you know it's a must ♪</i>

01:19:24.640 --> 01:19:28.440
<i>♪ Gotta have a friend in Jesus ♪</i>

01:19:28.520 --> 01:19:30.045
<i>♪ So you know that... ♪♪</i>

01:19:30.160 --> 01:19:31.730
Wouldn't be very Christian
if you stole my playbook

01:19:31.800 --> 01:19:33.484
now, Tandy, would it?

01:19:33.560 --> 01:19:35.164
Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:19:35.240 --> 01:19:37.163
No, it would not.

01:19:40.400 --> 01:19:43.882
<i>You know, I've always wanted
two things professionally:</i>

01:19:43.960 --> 01:19:48.284
to win a championship, and to
coach a truly great player.

01:19:48.360 --> 01:19:51.364
<i>You've done both,
so which is better?</i>

01:19:53.680 --> 01:19:56.365
Rings collect dust.

01:19:56.440 --> 01:20:00.286
That right there,
that lasts forever.

01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:07.164
<i>Two rivals, Banks and Woodlawn,
had their fall camp together.</i>

01:20:07.280 --> 01:20:09.726
<i>Both credit a spiritual
experience as the cause</i>

01:20:09.800 --> 01:20:11.928
<i>for the public show of unity.</i>

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:15.163
<i>The trouble is they can't
both enter the playoffs</i>

01:20:15.240 --> 01:20:17.083
because they're
in the same district.

01:20:17.160 --> 01:20:20.323
Many say this rule
is unfortunate, unfair,

01:20:20.400 --> 01:20:21.970
and should change.

01:20:27.640 --> 01:20:29.642
Mom, I got it.

01:20:31.400 --> 01:20:33.971
Hello, son.

01:20:34.040 --> 01:20:37.601
I'm not leaving here until
you decide to come to Alabama.

01:20:37.680 --> 01:20:39.523
Excuse me.

01:20:43.200 --> 01:20:45.009
Momma!

01:20:46.040 --> 01:20:47.929
Dear Lord,
we thank you for this food

01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:49.764
and for your provisions.

01:20:49.840 --> 01:20:53.322
Strengthen us with it
so that we might serve you.

01:20:53.400 --> 01:20:55.926
Amen.

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:59.686
And may I add, God in heaven,
help Tony see the light, Amen.

01:21:01.560 --> 01:21:03.130
<i>I do love corn.</i>

01:21:03.200 --> 01:21:04.725
<i>Not me!</i>

01:21:04.800 --> 01:21:06.689
<i>You don't like nothing!</i>

01:21:37.160 --> 01:21:38.764
Tony.

01:21:50.880 --> 01:21:54.202
We all do
what we do in life.

01:21:54.280 --> 01:21:56.282
Go our different ways.

01:21:59.240 --> 01:22:03.848
The idea of molding men,

01:22:03.920 --> 01:22:09.006
well, that means
a lot to me.

01:22:09.080 --> 01:22:11.686
And I want you to know
that I'm here to help

01:22:11.760 --> 01:22:13.762
no matter
what choice you make.

01:22:13.840 --> 01:22:18.767
And I think you
can feel that.

01:22:18.840 --> 01:22:21.844
Now, your momma...

01:22:25.840 --> 01:22:27.444
...showed me this.

01:22:27.520 --> 01:22:30.603
Said it was taped to a brick
thrown into this house.

01:22:30.680 --> 01:22:32.682
At my little brother.

01:22:37.320 --> 01:22:40.642
He didn't do nothing.

01:22:40.720 --> 01:22:43.883
That was all because of me.

01:22:50.800 --> 01:22:52.768
Tony, when I was
coming up here,

01:22:52.840 --> 01:22:59.246
I passed a football field
full of kids.

01:22:59.320 --> 01:23:05.168
I saw a young black boy wearin'
number 22, his head held high.

01:23:06.720 --> 01:23:08.722
That's also because of you.

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:15.129
And I wanna
say something, son.

01:23:18.120 --> 01:23:22.603
<i>You know the difference
between you and these people?</i>

01:23:25.400 --> 01:23:29.689
They're cowards,
and you ain't.

01:23:48.800 --> 01:23:50.484
<i>Here comes the senior tailback</i>

01:23:50.560 --> 01:23:52.210
<i>in his first game of the year.</i>

01:23:52.280 --> 01:23:54.362
<i>Of course,
expectations are high.</i>

01:23:54.440 --> 01:23:57.603
<i>Dozens of college scouts
and coaches are here watching.</i>

01:23:57.720 --> 01:24:00.200
<i>And, folks,
the atmosphere is electric.</i>

01:24:00.280 --> 01:24:04.365
<i>They all want to see
what this kid can do.</i>

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:12.570
Do you feel unstoppable
when you run?

01:24:12.640 --> 01:24:14.165
No, I just wanna
give Jesus Christ

01:24:14.240 --> 01:24:16.004
all the glory for giving us
another victory.

01:24:26.120 --> 01:24:27.645
<i>What do you think
about Jeff Rutledge?</i>

01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:29.290
Best QB in the state.

01:24:35.400 --> 01:24:36.686
<i>Fifteen second leeway,</i>

01:24:36.800 --> 01:24:38.450
<i>Alabama with one
time out remaining</i>

01:24:38.520 --> 01:24:40.090
<i>Rutledge on a roll.</i>

01:24:40.160 --> 01:24:43.164
<i>Looks down the middle,
and it is...</i>

01:24:43.720 --> 01:24:45.722
<i>Caught!
Touchdown!</i>

01:24:47.160 --> 01:24:49.083
<i>So, Jeff, what do you
think of Touchdown Tony?</i>

01:24:49.160 --> 01:24:50.730
I think Tony Nathan's
the best running back

01:24:50.800 --> 01:24:52.325
